'''Enveri''' (d. 1512?) was a 15th-century [[Ottoman Turks|Ottoman]] poet and historian.<ref>The Oxford History of Historical Writing 3,  José Rabasa,D. Daniel R. Woolf, page 197,  2012</ref> He wrote a famous Ottoman history in the [[Ottoman Turkish language]] named ''Dusturname'', the Constitutional Book (for Ottoman History). His work consists of 3730 verses and is based on three parts: the first is a universal [[Islamic history]], the second, which he is famous for, about the [[Aydinids]], and the third (842 verses) about the [[Ottoman Empire|Ottomans]]. Not much is known about his personal life.<ref>First Encyclopaedia of Islam: 1913-1936, M. Th Houtsma, page 482</ref>

